-- Vienna Airport shares rise 16 pct after IFM stake offer
-- 
-- Mon Oct 13, 2014 04:10AM EDT
-- None



VIENNA, Oct 13 (Reuters) - Vienna Airport <VIEV.VI> shares rose around 16 percent on Monday after it said that IFM Global Infrastructure Fund intended to buy a non-controlling minority stake of between 20 percent and 29.9 percent of the share capital.

IFM had offered 80 euros ($101.23) per share, a 29.7 percent premium over Friday's closing price, Vienna Airport said in a statement. [ID:nL6N0S810E]